  - ![+1](https://github.githubassets.com/assets/1f44d-41cb66fe1e22.png)2
  
  Answered by
  [vrothberg](https://github.com/vrothberg)[on Oct 3, 2023Oct 3, 2023](https://github.com/containers/podman/discussions/20218#discussioncomment-7173410)
  
  As mentioned above, there is a project to generate Quadlets: [https://github.com/k9withabone/podlet](https://github.com/k9withabone/podlet)
  
  I do not want to add that functionality to Podman as the ultimately goal is to move away from the workflow of generating systemd units based on existing containers. With Quadlet we aim at a Compose and K8s-like declarative workflow. Adding `podman generate quadlet` conflicts with that goal _and_ it would imply that new Quadlet features had to be added there as well.
  
  The current strategy is to deprecate `podman generate systemd`. That means that no new features will be added to `generate systemd` but only bug fixes.
  
  [View full answer](https://github.com/containers/podman/discussions/20218#discussioncomment-7173410)
  
