  | Quadlet requires users to create and manage multiple files (.container, .network, .volume) for each container.<br>This becomes much more complex and difficult to manage, especially if you have a large number of containers.<br>This also affects versioning and updates. A single compose-file previously made project tracking straightforward.<br>I am familiar with `podman generate` and the transition and effective use of quadlets will take time and testing.<br>Then one of the first points in the documentation is that when a quadlet is started, Podman often pulls new container images.<br>which can take a long time. Maybe a manual pre-pull of the images can help here... but it was not needed before.<br>I chose Podman for its simplicity over more complex solutions like k8s or k3s.<br>I suggest introducing a command like `podman generate quadlet` (which generates quadlet files and configs from an running podman project) to ease the transition and keep the simplicity that Podman offers. |
  
