  | > > Install my .container file to /etc/containers/systemd/ as the documentation tells me to do \[...\]<br>> <br>> That depends whether you want to run the .service as root or not. `/etc/containers/systemd` is only accessible as root, `/etc/containers/systemd/users/` and `.../$(UID)` is accessible for rootless users (plus the `$HOME/.config` dirs).<br>Adding a .container or a .service file to /etc/containers/systemd does't add anything to 'systemctl list-units' after doing 'systemctl daemon-reload'. I can relate to what was shared earlier by [@jafd](https://github.com/jafd). It's a frustrating experience and a waste of time. |
  
