  | Please note that Quadlet is not shipped as a standalone solution, it is part of Podman and as such is installed along with it for quite some while.<br>As for usage (I know I'm biased, but), I prefer it over script files. For example, sometimes for development I need to run a redis server. So, I have a Quadlet file `redis.container` in `~/.config/containers/systemd`:<br>```<br>Image=docker.io/redis/redis-stack:latest<br>PublishPort=6379:6379<br>PublishPort=8001:8001<br>ContainerName=redis<br>```<br>Then all I need to do to start or stop the service is to use systemctl:<br>```<br># Start the service<br>systemctl--user start redis<br># Stop the service<br>systemctl--user start redis<br>```<br>Without having to remember where is the script, what was its name, etc. |
  
