  | --- |
  | Your assumption is Wrong. Podman and CRI-O need to co-exists. CRI-O is a dedicated container engine for running kubernetes workloads, supporting everything kubernetes needs.<br>Podman and a single purpose single node container engine which while it support k8s yaml, it does not work with kubelet and support most other k8s features, and has no intention too.<br>Podman while not a daemon requires systemd to manage its containerized services. Quadlet is a tool to make this happen.<br>There is not requirement to use k8s.yaml for defining complex applications, it is just an added benefit that Podman supports it.<br>Quadlet can run containers, pods and manage volumes, networks, images and builds all without k8s.<br>Podman can also run pods and containers via CLI.<br>Podman service supports compose functionality at the API level.<br>There are two implementations of compose docker-compose and podman-compose (Which is a separate project then Podman, and not worked on by the Podman maintainers). Podman can work with both docker-compose of podman-compose. |
  
